CALIFORNIA RIGHTS
California residents have certain rights with respect to the personal information collected by businesses.  If you are a California resident, you may exercise the following rights regarding your personal information, subject to certain exceptions and limitations defined in the regulations:

The right to know the categories and specific pieces of personal information we collect, use, disclose, and sell about you, the categories of sources from which we collected your personal information, our purposes for collecting or selling your personal information, the categories of your personal information that we have either sold or disclosed for a business purpose, and the categories of third parties with which we have shared personal information;

CALIFORNIA RIGHTS
California residents have certain rights with respect to the personal information collected by businesses.  If you are a California resident, you may exercise the following rights regarding your personal information, subject to certain exceptions and limitations defined in the regulations:

The right to know the categories and specific pieces of personal information we collect, use, disclose, and sell about you, the categories of sources from which we collected your personal information, our purposes for collecting or selling your personal information, the categories of your personal information that we have either sold or disclosed for a business purpose, and the categories of third parties with which we have shared personal information;

We used this information for various commercial and business purposes, including: Advertising and marketing analytics products and services;
Audience measurement
User authentication and identity resolution
Auditing related to our interactions with you;
Legal compliance;
Detecting and protecting against security incidents, fraud, and illegal activity;
Debugging;
Performing services (for us or our service provider) such as account servicing, processing orders and payments, and analytics;
Internal research for technological improvement;
Internal operations;
Activities to maintain and improve our products and services; and
Other one-time uses.

We may use the digital identifiers, Internet activity, and other information linked to that information for the following purposes:

Advertising and marketing products to you;
Analytics and measurement services;
Auditing related to our interactions with you;
Legal compliance;
Detecting and protecting against security incidents, fraud, and illegal activity;
Debugging;
Performing services (for us or our service provider) such as account servicing, processing orders and payments, and analytics;
Internal research for technological improvement;
Internal operations;
Activities to maintain and improve our services; and
Other one-time uses.

DISCLOSURE & SALE – RESEARCH, MARKETING ANALYTICS, AND ADVERTISING
As further set forth below, in the past 12 months, we have collected, disclosed, and sold California consumers’ personal information to third parties for business or commercial purposes as identified in the list below.

As part of our commercial marketing analytics and advertising products and services, in the past 12 months, we have collected online identifiers (such as device identifiers, cookie IDs, and geolocation information), demographic information (such as gender), transaction information (such as products you may have considered purchasing), Internet activity (such as websites you visited and advertisements you have seen), inferences about your interests and preferences, and other information we may link to this information (such as responses to survey questions you agreed to answer for us).

We collected this information from a variety of sources, such as consumers, our clients, web browsers and mobile apps, service providers, advertising networks, and other consumer data resellers.

We used this information for various commercial and business purposes, including: Advertising and marketing analytics products and services;
Audience measurement
User authentication and identity resolution
Auditing related to our interactions with you;
Legal compliance;
Detecting and protecting against security incidents, fraud, and illegal activity;
Debugging;
Performing services (for us or our service provider) such as account servicing, processing orders and payments, and analytics;
Internal research for technological improvement;
Internal operations;
Activities to maintain and improve our products and services; and
Other one-time uses.
We disclosed the categories of information discussed above with certain categories of third parties, such as advertising networks, advertising agencies and marketing companies, social networks, analytics providers, service providers, and consumer data resellers.  Additionally, we may sell some of this personal information to our clients and partners, including advertising networks, advertising agencies and marketing companies, social networks, analytics providers, consumer data resellers, and clients in various industries, such as: apparel & accessory, automotive, business services agencies, telecommunication services, consumer packaged goods, health & wellness services, educational institutions, electronics & technology, financial services, food & beverage, gift products, lifestyle & interest products, media & entertainment, publishing, travel & hospitality, government, politics and advocacy, and other similar organizations.

