DISCLOSURE & SALE – CORPORATE WEBSITE
As part of our corporate website functions, in the past 12 months, we collected personal contact information (such as name or email address), digital identifiers (such as device identifier, cookie ID, and IP address), and your Internet activity (such as what pages are visited on our website), and other information we may link to this information.  We collected this information from consumers and their web browsers when consumers provided it to ask questions or otherwise contact us, or when entities requested services from us.  We use the contact information we collect through our website to contact consumers to respond to questions, troubleshoot issues, resolve disputes, legal compliance, internal research and operations, and to improve our website, contact about employment applications and opportunities or recruitment, and to market products and services to you.

We may use the digital identifiers, Internet activity, and other information linked to that information for the following purposes:

Advertising and marketing products to you;
Analytics and measurement services;
Auditing related to our interactions with you;
Legal compliance;
Detecting and protecting against security incidents, fraud, and illegal activity;
Debugging;
Performing services (for us or our service provider) such as account servicing, processing orders and payments, and analytics;
Internal research for technological improvement;
Internal operations;
Activities to maintain and improve our services; and
Other one-time uses.
We may disclose the contact information we collect to our service providers, government agencies if required by law to do so, or third parties you instruct us to share it with.  We may also disclose the digital identifiers, Internet activity, and other information linked to that information with service providers, advertising networks, marketing and advertising companies, social networks, and other third parties who aid us in the performance of our advertising and marketing services.

